text: A fourth ( although not strictly monophyletic ) clade ( D ) of viral sequences from Australian cats contained three VP2 sequences identical to that of an FPV vaccine strain ( Purevax ; Genbank accession no . EU498680 ) and two sequences that are very closely related to the vaccine strain . In one of these , from a 6 - week - old kitten with acute vomiting and failure to gain weight , the vaccine strain was unlikely to be the cause of the cat ' s clinical signs . FPL was suspected because a multiplex qPCR faecal panel was positive for Giard spp . and Canine protoparvovirus 1 . However , the cat , from Canberra in the Australian Capital Territory , had been vaccinated 16 days before with the same MLV vaccine strain .
